xamples in this book serve as a cross-section of these perspectives of modernization: the fifth Paris World Exhibition of 1900, which attracted 50 million visitors, the discussion of social questions in selected cultural journals as well as the reactions to the upheaval in colonial China.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aAmerican periodicalsxHistoryy19th centuryvCongresses. 0aEuropean periodicalsxHistoryy19th centuryvCongresses. 0aLabor movementxHistoryy19th centuryxPress coveragezEurope. 0aNineteen hundred, A.DxPress coveragevCongresses. 4a19./ 20. Jahrhundert. 4aArbeiterbewegung. 4aChina. 4aJahrhundertwende. 4aKulturzeitschriften. 4aPariser Weltausstellung. 7aHISTORY / Europe / General.2bisacsh  a19th/20th Centuries.  aChina.  aCultural Journals.  aLabor Movement.  aParis World Exhibition.  aTurn of the Century.1 aBROCKMEIER, ALKE, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDETERING, HEINRICH, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDetering, Heinrich, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFRIEDE, SUSANNE, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGENTZ, NATASCHA, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGLASER, BRIGITTE, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGREBING, HELGA, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGÖSKE, DANIEL, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHOFF, KARIN, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJÜRGENSEN, CHRISTOPH, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJürgensen, Christoph.1 aMUSSER, RICARDA, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMÖLK, ULRICH, ec